T|12 ·|0|The production flow for short-form clips — the Kanban equivalent of the cn Pipeline, but for Shorts, feeding the Shorts distribution page.
T|12 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|Move short-form cn from idea/clip through to ready-to-distribute. Where the cn Pipeline handles long-form, the Short Pipeline manages the lifecycle of shorts (often derived from long-form videos, e.g. "follow-up Shorts" generated in YouTube Studio).
T|Purp|1|
X|What|0|A staged board (idea → cut/clip → ct/cp → ready) for short clips.
X|What|1|Cards feed the Shorts page (13) where the finished clip is uploaded and distributed to each platform.
X|What|2|Connects to YouTube Studio, which can spin off follow-up Shorts from a long-form transcript.
X|What|3|
T|Rela|0|Upstream of Shorts (13) — the Short Pipeline prepares; the Shorts page distributes.
T|Rela|1|Parallel in structure to cn Pipeline (08).
